ABOUT THE ROLE

As a Global Sourcing and Supply Chain Manager (GSSM) at Biofire, you’ll sit at the intersection of Biofire’s operations and engineering communities, and effectively balance the needs of both groups to enable development, industrailization and sustainment of Biofire’s current supply base as well as ensure the success of new product launches. You will work in close coordination with Product Engineering, Supplier Industrialization / Quality Engineers (SIE/SQE) and Suppliers to execute effective, creative and smart supply chain strategies to achieve production goals.

To succeed, you will need to effectively team with this cross-functional team across a product’s life cycle to ensure an uninterrupted, on time supply of mechanical fabricated parts to Biofire’s production line. If you’re excited about building a supply chain from the ground up, we’d love to hear from you.

KEY RESPONSIBILITIES

Day-to-day responsibilities of the role will include:

 - [GSM] Own the commercial relationship with Biofire’s existing mechanical fabricated parts Suppliers;

 - [GSM] In conjunction with Engineering and Supplier Industrialization, own the identification and qualification of new Suppliers / new Parts;

 - [GSM] Own cost negotiations, continuity of supply, risk management for the mechanical fabricated parts category;

 - [GSM] In conjunction with Engineering and Supplier Quality, drive operational and cost efficiencies through process or design change, as well as overall project execution;

 - [GSM] Conduct routine business reviews with mechanical fabricated parts Suppliers, addressing key indicators of Supplier performance (First Pass Yield, On-Time / In-Full deliveries), root causing sub-optimal performance and leading corrective actions;

 - [GSSM] Develop a nuanced understanding of the mechanical fabricated parts category landscape in order to forecast industry trends and gauge emerging competitive forces;

 - [GSSM] Identify changes in Buyer and Supplier power and use industry dynamics to Biofire’s advantage;

 - [GSSM] Perform Supplier financial research, spend analysis and ad-hoc financial analysis for strategic procurement;

 - [GSSM] Effectively work with mechanical fabricated parts Suppliers to negotiate optimal terms for sourcing;

 - [GSSM] Intuitively grasp the trade-offs between cost, volume, and quality in order to strike agreements that meet Biofire’s performance criteria

