ABOUT THE ROLE

As a Senior Forward Deployed Engineer, Internal Systems at Biofire, you will play a pivotal role in developing and implementing our internal systems strategy—partnering with teams across operations, production, and manufacturing to understand current workflows, uncover pain points, and translate insights into a prioritized execution plan. We are looking for someone who is highly autonomous, deeply curious, and comfortable moving from ambiguity to action to help strengthen the systems that power our day-to-day execution.

To succeed you will need to be able to dive deep into system usage, conduct user research, and ship meaningful improvements quickly—including producing a clear roadmap and executing baseline features that move us toward a minimum lovable product. You will need to be an evidence-driven problem solver, who is eager to build internal systems that improve operational workflows and make data a trusted source of truth. If you’re excited about helping to solve mission-critical challenges, we encourage you to apply.

 


KEY RESPONSIBILITIES

Day-to-day responsibilities of the role will include:

 - Develop and implement internal systems strategy by collaborating with stakeholders to understand current state usage, pain points, and workflow gaps; documenting findings and recommendations clearly;

 - Conduct user research and deep product/system discovery to develop a data-validated, prioritized action plan for internal system improvements;

 - Lead assessment, ranking, and execution of a roadmap for internal systems issues and features;

 - Own feature execution by rapidly prototyping, iterating, and delivering baseline feature improvements on the path to a minimum lovable product;

 - Establish and operate a structured feedback loop and request intake process for internal users; triage requests, clarify problem statements, and align intake with internal systems planning and prioritization;

 - Maintain documentation and enable adoption by creating/updating process flows and training users (new and existing) on system changes and workflow optimization based on real use cases;

 - Strong communicator and listener who can translate user needs into clear requirements, tailor solutions to real-world constraints, and drive alignment through documentation and training.

 


