 - Work with system owners and cross-functional teams to understand internal workflows, current systems, pain points, and operational needs;

 - Develop practical technical plans for internal systems projects, including scope, approach, dependencies, and tradeoffs;

 - Build, improve, and maintain internal tools, integrations, and workflows that help teams operate more efficiently and with better information;

 - Connect commercial platforms and custom applications so business, manufacturing, and operations teams can rely on consistent workflows and data;

 - Improve existing systems by making them easier to operate, troubleshoot, and support;

 - Document system behavior, technical decisions, and handoff details clearly for the teams that use and maintain these systems;

 - Support changes to legacy workflows and systems as Biofire’s internal needs evolve.

 


